.TH UPAPASTA 1 "2026-05" "upapasta 0.25.0" "User Manual"
.SH NAME
upapasta \- automated Usenet uploader
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B upapasta
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIinput\fR [\fIinput\fR ...]
.br
.B upapasta
\fB\-\-config\fR
.br
.B upapasta
\fB\-\-stats\fR
.br
.B upapasta
\fB\-\-test\-connection\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B upapasta
automates the full Usenet upload pipeline: NFO generation, optional RAR5
creation, PAR2 parity generation, upload via nyuu without staging in /tmp,
and NZB post-processing with corrected subjects. Zero Python dependencies \(em
system binaries only.
.PP
On the first run, an interactive wizard creates
.I ~/.config/upapasta/.env
with your NNTP server credentials.
.SH ESSENTIAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-profile \fINAME\fR
Uses
.I ~/.config/upapasta/<NAME>.env
as configuration instead of the default .env.
.TP
.B \-\-watch
Daemon mode: monitors the input directory continuously and processes new items
automatically. Exit with Ctrl+C. Incompatible with \fB\-\-each\fR and
\fB\-\-season\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-each
Processes each file in the folder individually. Each file becomes a separate
release with its own NZB.
.TP
.B \-\-season
Like \fB\-\-each\fR, but also generates a single NZB containing the entire
season at the end.
.TP
.B \-\-obfuscate
Reversible obfuscation: random names for RAR/PAR2 files before upload.
The NZB is processed to restore original names in subjects.
.TP
.B \-\-strong\-obfuscate
Maximum obfuscation: random names for files, PAR2, and NZB subjects.
Implies \fB\-\-obfuscate\fR. Requires manual renaming or via PAR2 after download.
.TP
.B \-\-password [\fIPASSWORD\fR]
RAR password, injected into the NZB for automatic extraction.
Automatically implies \fB\-\-rar\fR. Without an argument, generates a random
16-character password.
.TP
.B \-\-rar
Creates RAR5 files before upload. Disabled by default.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Simulates the entire process without creating or sending files.
.TP
.B \-\-jobs \fIN\fR
Number of parallel uploads when multiple inputs are provided.
Default: 1 (sequential).
.SH ADJUSTMENT OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-par\-profile \fI{fast,balanced,safe}\fR
PAR2 profile: fast=5%, balanced=10% (default), safe=20%.
.TP
.B \-r \fIN\fR, \-\-redundancy \fIN\fR
PAR2 redundancy in percentage. Overwrites \fB\-\-par\-profile\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-files
Keeps RAR and PAR2 after upload.
.TP
.B \-\-log\-file \fIPATH\fR
Writes full session log to the specified file.
.TP
.B \-\-upload\-retries \fIN\fR
Extra upload attempts in case of failure, with exponential backoff. Default: 0.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enables debug logging with ISO timestamps.
.TP
.B \-\-resume
Resumes interrupted upload by detecting already posted files via partial NZB.
.SH ADVANCED OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-backend \fI{parpar,par2}\fR
Backend for PAR2 generation. Default: parpar (faster, supports subfolders).
.TP
.B \-\-filepath\-format \fI{common,keep,basename,outrel}\fR
How parpar records paths in .par2 files. \fBcommon\fR (default) preserves relative
subfolders. Ignored when \fB\-\-backend par2\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-parpar\-args \fISTR\fR
Extra args passed to parpar, tokenized via shlex.
.TP
.B \-\-nyuu\-args \fISTR\fR
Extra args passed to nyuu, tokenized via shlex.
.TP
.B \-\-rename\-extensionless
Renames files without extension to .bin before upload (reverts at the end).
Prevents SABnzbd from adding .txt to these files.
.TP
.B \-\-skip\-upload
Generates RAR/PAR2/NFO without uploading to Usenet.
.TP
.B \-\-skip\-par
Skips parity generation.
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-force
Overwrites existing RAR/PAR2.
.TP
.B \-\-nzb\-conflict \fI{rename,overwrite,fail}\fR
Behavior when an NZB with the same name already exists. Default: rename.
.TP
.B \-\-env\-file \fIPATH\fR
Alternative path for the .env file.
.SH UTILITIES
.TP
.B \-\-config
Opens the interactive configuration wizard. Preserves existing values (Enter
keeps current value).
.TP
.B \-\-stats
Displays aggregated statistics from upload history: total sent, categories,
GB per month, average duration.
.TP
.B \-\-test\-connection
Validates connectivity with the NNTP server: CONNECT/LOGIN/QUIT handshake.
.TP
.B \-\-insecure
Disables SSL certificate verification in \fB\-\-test\-connection\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Default upload (recommended 2026 flow):
.B upapasta Folder/ \-\-obfuscate \-\-backend parpar \-\-filepath\-format common \-\-par\-profile safe
.TP
Single file without RAR:
.B upapasta Episode.S01E01.mkv
.TP
Multiple inputs in parallel:
.B upapasta Folder1/ Folder2/ Folder3/ \-\-jobs 3
.TP
Season with consolidated NZB:
.B upapasta /tv/The.Boys.S04/ \-\-season \-\-obfuscate
.TP
Upload with RAR password:
.B upapasta Folder/ \-\-password "MyP@ssw0rd"
.TP
Daemon monitoring folder:
.B upapasta /downloads/ \-\-watch \-\-watch\-stable 120
.TP
Resume interrupted upload:
.B upapasta Folder/ \-\-resume
.TP
Simulate with subprocess logging:
.B upapasta Folder/ \-\-dry\-run \-\-verbose
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/upapasta/.env
Main configuration: NNTP credentials, group, article size, and options.
.TP
.I ~/.config/upapasta/<NAME>.env
Alternative profile loaded via \fB\-\-profile <NAME>\fR.
.TP
.I ~/.config/upapasta/history.jsonl
Upload catalog (append-only JSONL). Records timestamp, name, RAR password,
size, category, group, and NZB path.
.TP
.I ~/.config/upapasta/nzb/
Archived NZBs via hardlink (organized by timestamp).
.TP
.I ~/.config/upapasta/logs/
Session logs generated automatically (one per run).
.TP
.I .upapasta-state.json
Resume state file, saved alongside the partial NZB during upload.
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
Variables read from .env (or exported in shell):
.TP
.B NNTP_HOST, NNTP_PORT, NNTP_SSL, NNTP_USER, NNTP_PASS, NNTP_CONNECTIONS
Main NNTP server configuration.
.TP
.B NNTP_HOST_2 ... NNTP_HOST_9
Optional failover servers. Missing fields inherit from the primary server.
.TP
.B USENET_GROUP
Upload group(s). Comma for pool with random selection.
.TP
.B ARTICLE_SIZE
Maximum article size. Default: 700K.
.TP
.B NZB_OUT, NZB_OUT_DIR
Template and output directory for .nzb.
.TP
.B POST_UPLOAD_SCRIPT
Script executed after successful upload (receives UPAPASTA_* variables).
.TP
.B WEBHOOK_URL
URL for post-upload notification (Discord, Slack, Telegram, or generic).
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B nyuu
NNTP upload. Install: npm install \-g nyuu
.TP
.B parpar
PAR2 generation (recommended). Install: pip install parpar
.TP
.B par2
Alternative to parpar. Install: apt install par2
.TP
.B rar
RAR5 (required only with \fB\-\-rar\fR). Install: apt install rar
.TP
.B ffprobe
Video metadata in NFO (optional). Install: apt install ffmpeg
.TP
.B mediainfo
Technical media info in NFO (optional). Install: apt install mediainfo
.SH EXIT CODE
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Generic error.
.TP
.B 2
PAR2 generation error.
.TP
.B 3
Upload error or NZB conflict.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by user (Ctrl+C).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nyuu (1),
.BR par2 (1),
.BR rar (1)
.PP
